 lobell supports this concern and he shares his results in an interview with reuters climate trends and global crop production since 1980 prioritizing investments in food security under a changing climate climate and agriculture models impacts and adaptation strategies reuters crop scientists now fret about heat not just water search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest extreme heat shortens wheat growing season reduces yield january 29 2012 fse fsi stanford news greater crop diversity and wild genes needed to feed growing population october 28 2011 fsi stanford fse news fse fellow david lobell quoted in climatewire article on preserving crop wild relatives fsi stanford fse in the news climatewire on december 10 2010 from russia more heat less wheat david lobell climate central on august 6 2010 global warming in the last 20 years has led to a decline in crop yields resultlng in an annual loss of $5 billion says fse scholars lobell and field march 19 2007 fse in the news nature is the global carbon market working february 7 2007 pesd in the news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
